# extra-commands — additional commands for weka-log-collector
#
# Add custom commands here, one per line.
# Blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored.
# Commands already collected by the active profile are skipped automatically.
#
# These commands run on the ORCHESTRATOR NODE ONLY when --extra-commands is passed.
# Output is saved under cluster/extra/ in the archive.
#
# BLOCKED (skipped with a warning):
#   System:    rm, rmdir, dd, mkfs, mkfs.*, shred, wipefs, fdisk, parted, gdisk,
#              sgdisk, reboot, shutdown, halt, poweroff
#   Weka:      weka cluster stop-io/start-io/update,
#              weka cluster container deactivate/remove/requested-action,
#              weka cluster drive deactivate/remove,
#              weka local stop/restart/reset-data,
#              weka fs remove, weka fs group remove,
#              weka org remove, weka user remove,
#              weka security, weka smb cluster destroy, weka agent uninstall
#   systemctl: stop, start, restart, disable, enable, mask, daemon-reload
#
# Examples:
# /weka/reader/histogram --slot 0
# cat /proc/meminfo
